Subject: [TSMC] AIC applied permission error
Description: Enter the user query on the homepage, click permission in the report box on the right, an error will pop up, and the relevant logs and error screenshots have been uploaded.
DevOps_Steps_to_Reproduce__c:
1. Search a user in AIC and click it.
2. On the right pane, click on permissions
What_We_Know__c: The customer is currently using EOS and EOL version 11.0.0.231 of StealthAudit. When they try to view "permissions" against a user searched in AIC, they are observing STATUS 500 code.
Next_Steps__c: Bug is resolved as per Bug Fix list and after confirming from the dev team in SWAT. Customer will update and let us know. However, they dont know the exact date for starting the upgrade process. This ticket will be closed as per confirmation of the customer
Solution_Comment__c: Customer has been recommended to upgrade the product
